    <h2>Parameters</h2>
    <p>The parameters can be configured through the Trifid configuration or through query parameters:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Simplified mode (<a href="/adams/gomez?simplifiedMode=true">example with Gomez, simplifiedMode=true</a>)</li>
      <li>Compact mode (<a href="/person/amy-farrah-fowler?compactMode=true">example with Amy, compactMode=true</a>)</li>
      <li>Embed blank nodes (<a href="/adams/gomez?embedBlankNodes=true">example with Gomez, embedBlankNodes=true</a>)</li>
      <li>Technical cues (<a href="/person/amy-farrah-fowler?technicalCues=true">example with Amy, technicalCues=true</a>)</li>
      <li>Embed ordered lists (<a href="/adams/gomez?embedLists=true">example with Gomez, embedLists=true</a>)</li>
      <li>Highlight language (<a href="/adams/eudora?highlightLanguage=es">example with Eudora, highlightLanguage=es</a>)</li>
      <li>Show named graphs (<a href="/adams/eudora?showNamedGraphs=true">example with Eudora, showNamedGraphs=true</a>)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Tools</h2>
    <p>This instance also comes with the following plugins:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/sparql/">YASGUI</a>: allows you to query your SPARQL endpoint</li>
    </ul>
